PN,42101
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FA mother of a teenager who died within
OL,7,F48 hours of falling ill from
OL,8,Fmeningitis B is urging people to be
OL,9,Fvigilant should they show any symptoms.
OL,11,FJoanne Bolam, of Newcastle, said her
OL,12,F19-year-old son Jack began feeling
OL,13,Funwell and just two days later a life
OL,14,Fsupport machine he was on was switched
OL,15,Foff.
OL,17,FDoctors said he had contracted
OL,18,Fmeningitis B.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FAs more cases have been confirmed amid
OL,7,Fan outbreak of the infection in Kent,
OL,8,FJoanne is warning others to react
OL,9,Fquickly if they notice symptoms.
OL,11,FShe told ITV Tyne Tees: "That day just
OL,12,Fwrecked our whole world. We didn't
OL,13,Fhave long to know anything about
OL,14,Fmeningitis, let alone that he was
OL,15,Fgoing to die from it."
OL,17,F"My whole world literally just fell
OL,18,Fapart within 48 hours," she continued,
OL,19,Fadding: "Our world was ruined in less
OL,20,Fthan 48 hours because of meningitis."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FJoanne said her son was a very healthy
OL,7,Fteenager who regularly played rugby
OL,8,Fand went to the gym. His symptoms
OL,9,Fstarted with dizziness, shivers, and
OL,10,Fvomiting before he was admitted to
OL,11,Fintensive care.
OL,13,F"He was a big, strong lad," she said.
OL,14,F"Nobody could've seen how quick he
OL,15,Fwent downhill and it was absolutely
OL,16,Fhorrific to watch."
OL,18,FSharing Jack's story previously with
OL,19,Fthe charity Meningitis Now, Joanne
OL,20,Fdescribed the speed of her son's
OL,21,Fillness.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,F"Jack went to work at 5.50pm," she
OL,7,Fsaid. "He rang his sister at 6.40pm to
OL,8,Fsay he felt dizzy and could she pick
OL,9,Fhim up. He was home 10 minutes later
OL,10,Fand I tucked him up in bed with a cup
OL,11,Fof tea as he said he was freezing.
OL,13,F"At 8pm he had vomited and his sister
OL,14,Fwas saying 'get up, mam's coming up'.
OL,15,FMyself and Jack's dad and sisters went
OL,16,Fupstairs to see what was wrong.
OL,18,F"Jack started convulsing so we rang
OL,19,F999. He was admitted to the Royal
OL,20,FVictoria Infirmary at 9pm.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,F"At 10pm the consultant suggested I
OL,7,Fget my husband there straight away. By
OL,8,F11pm Jack was in the Intensive Care
OL,9,FUnit. The consultant then told us Jack
OL,10,Fwasn't responding to treatment. Jack
OL,11,Fwas on monitors - there were machines
OL,12,Fand tubes everywhere. That was
OL,13,FThursday 30th January 2025."
OL,15,FTwo days later on 1 February 2025,
OL,16,FJoanne said the family were asked to
OL,17,Fsit with Jack before he died at 2.05pm.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FJoanne assumed Jack's symptoms came
OL,7,Ffrom a cold, particularly because he
OL,8,Fdid not have a rash, and said having
OL,9,Fmeningitis never crossed her mind.
OL,11,FAlthough there are no reported cases
OL,12,Fin the North East, her message now is
OL,13,Fto look out for the symptoms of
OL,14,Fmeningitis.
OL,16,FSpeaking from the rugby club where she
OL,17,Fsaid Jack was at his "happiest",
OL,18,FJoanne said: "Be vigilant. If you
OL,19,Fthink that it's not just a cold or a
OL,20,Fcough or a virus, go to your doctor."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FMeningitis B, the suspected strain of
OL,7,Fbacteria behind an outbreak in Kent,
OL,8,Fis the most common form of meningitis
OL,9,Fin the UK and is the infection that
OL,10,Fled to Jack's death.
OL,12,FWhat are the symptoms of meningitis?
OL,14,FAccording to Meningitis Now, symptoms
OL,15,Fof meningitis can be confused with
OL,16,Fcommon cold, including headaches,
OL,17,Ffevers, confusion, and vomiting.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FThe charity says that as the disease
OL,7,Fprogresses, other symptoms may emerge,
OL,8,Fincluding a stiff neck, an aversion to
OL,9,Fbright lights, and a rash that does
OL,10,Fnot fade when pressure is applied.
OL,12,FThere is set order to the symptoms and
OL,13,Fthey may not appear at the same time.
OL,15,FDr Tom Nutt, CEO of Meningitis Now,
OL,16,Fdescribes the symptoms of meningitis
OL,18,FHow is meningitis spread?
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FDr Tom Nutt, CEO of Meningitis Now,
OL,7,Fsaid: "Meningitis is spread by a
OL,8,Fbacteria, in some cases viruses, which
OL,9,Fare mostly carried harmlessly in the
OL,10,Fback of our noses and throats."
OL,12,FIt can be passed on through kissing,
OL,13,Fsharing drinks, coughing, and sneezing.
OL,15,F"You won't necessarily catch
OL,16,Fmeningitis just by sitting next to
OL,17,Fsomeone," Dr Nutt said. "There needs
OL,18,Fto be prolonged exposure, and even
OL,19,Fthen it's not the case that you'll
OL,20,Fnecessarily get the disease."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FIs there a vaccine for meningitis?
OL,8,FThere are a number of vaccines that
OL,9,Fcan protect against meningitis. These
OL,10,Finclude the MenACWY and MenB vaccines.
OL,12,FTeenagers, sixth formers and those
OL,13,Fgoing to university for the first time
OL,14,Fcan have the MenACWY vaccine, which
OL,15,Fcan help protect against meningitis
OL,16,Fand sepsis.
OL,18,FThe MenACWY vaccine can be given up to
OL,19,Fthe age of 25 if it has been missed
OL,20,Fand is also available to some
OL,21,Findividuals who are at greater risk.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FThe Men B vaccine has been offered to
OL,7,Fbabies since 2015, meaning most older
OL,8,Fteenagers and university students have
OL,9,Fnot received the jab.
OL,11,FPrivate vaccinations are available at
OL,12,Fsome travel clinics, private GP
OL,13,Fpractices and pharmacies.
OL,15,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,16,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,17,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,18,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,20,FWhat precautions can be taken?
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42112
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1773864688
OL,3,C'Our world was ruined in less than 48
OL,4,Chours because of meningitis'
OL,6,FGood basic hygiene including
OL,7,Fhandwashing and regularly cleaning
OL,8,Fsurfaces is important. People may also
OL,9,Favoid sharing drinks and other items
OL,10,Fthat come into contact with mouths.
OL,12,FHow is it treated?
OL,14,FOnce a diagnosis is confirmed,
OL,15,Fmeningitis can be treated fairly
OL,16,Feasily with antibiotics. Acting fast
OL,17,Fis important.
OL,19,FDr Nutt said: "The sooner people get
OL,20,Fthose antibiotics, the likelihood of a
OL,21,Fbetter outcome is improved."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
